description: President Van der Bellen stayed at a Vienna restaurant beyond the mandated closing time of 23:00.
title: Coronavirus: Austrian president 'sorry' for breaking lockdown rules
title_page: Coronavirus: Austrian president 'sorry' for breaking lockdown rules - BBC News
maintext: It was also one of the first to begin easing its restrictions. Gatherings of up to 10 people have been allowed since the start of May, and public parks, small shops, DIY stores and garden centres have been open since last month.
